      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: To the Sports Editor:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>After the second Yankee game of the season, I wanted to write George Steinbrenner a laconic letter: Wait Until Next Year. But I thought you would think me presumptuous and premature.</p>
        <p>I just read that the Yankee ''brain trust'' is planning to make Deion Sanders the leadoff hitter. I did not know he had a great knack for getting on base, with a hit, walk, hit with a ball. I did not know he knew the strike zone as well as the umpires.</p>
        <p>And this same ''brain trust'' is planning to move Roberto Kelly from his second slot. In the last two weeks, Kelly is batting .359 in that second slot.</p>
        <p>I now can tell Mr. Steinbrenner Wait Until Next Year as I look into my crystal ball.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL F.X. GRIECO</p>
        <p>West Orange, N.J.</p>
      </block>
